sentences: Tahira Syed [sic] (Urdu: طاہرہ سيد) (born 1958, Lahore) is a Pakistani ghazal and folk singer.
After two years of rigorous classical music training by Akhtar Hussain, Syed was instructed in geet and ghazal by her mother.
Syed first appeared on air in 1968–1969 on Radio Pakistan, and then on Pakistan Television.
In April 1985, she appeared on the cover of National Geographic magazine.
She received the Pakistan Television Lifetime Achievement Award, and the Pride of Performance Award from the President of Pakistan on 23 March 2013.
In 1972, she won the Nigar Award for Best Female Playback Singer.

Syed continues to perform at diverse events such as a "ghazal evening" in Dallas, Texas, U.S., a tribute to Faiz Ahmed Faiz in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, U.S., and at the Faiz International Festival in Lahore.
Syed was married to lawyer Naeem Bukhari for 15 years (1975-1990) before their separation and divorce; they had two children.
